      • resolve

        public IpSpaceAssignment resolve(java.util.Set<Location> locations,
                                 SpecifierContext ctxt)
        Description copied from interface: IpSpaceSpecifier
        Resolve the specifier into concrete IpSpaces.
        Specified by:
        resolve in interface IpSpaceSpecifier
        Parameters:
        locations - The @{link Location}s for which concrete IpSpaces are needed. Which concrete IpSpace is specified may (or may not) vary with Location.
        ctxt - Information about the network that may be used to resolve concrete IpSpaces.
        Returns:
        A multimap that assigns IpSpaces to sets of the input Location. It is required that the set of values of the multimap matches exactly the input Locations, and that no Location is assigned more than one IpSpace.
